jrobots.simulation.simulationObjects.launchables

Class Rocket

  • java.lang.Object
    • jrobots.simulation.simulationObjects.launchables.Launchable
      • jrobots.simulation.simulationObjects.launchables.Rocket
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Directable

    public class Rocket
extends Launchable
implements Directable
    Rockets are Directable Projectiles.

    Features are:

    • Directability: Through setBearing
    • Detonation on impact (like Projectile)
    • Indefinite lifetime (lifetime ends if link to Directable breaks)
    See Also:

      • detonate

        public void detonate()
        Description copied from class: Launchable
        Is set on collision with an object (if the Launchable participates in collisions). This marks that the Launchable is removed from the simulation.

        Necessity: Directables need to store the information that they are removed from the simulation, so that the Panzer they originate from can remove its uplink.

        Specified by:
        detonate in interface Directable
        Specified by:
        detonate in class Launchable
